2. Glutes prime

Top Dumbbell Glute-Focused Exercises
1. Dumbbell Hip Thrust

Place upper back on bench, dumbbell on hips.

Drive hips up and squeeze glutes hard.

One of the best glute-building movements.

2. Dumbbell Glute Bridge

Similar to hip thrust but floor-based.

Great if you don‚Äôt have a bench.

Very glute-dominant.

3. Dumbbell Bulgarian Split Squat (Glute-Biased)

Big forward lean.

Larger step forward.

Puts more load on glutes vs quads.

4. Dumbbell Romanian Deadlift (Glute-Focused)

Slightly softer knees.

Push hips back.

Stretch-loaded glute movement.

5. Dumbbell Step-Ups (Glute-Biased)

Step high.

Lean forward slightly as you step.

Drive through heel of the planted foot.

6. Dumbbell Walking Lunges (Glute-Biased)

Long strides.

Lean forward a bit.

Targets glutes much more than short-stride lunges.

7. Dumbbell Sumo Squat

Wide stance, dumbbell held between legs.

More glute/inner thigh than standard squats.

8. Dumbbell Kickstand RDL

Rear foot lightly behind you.

Front leg does most of the work.

Great unilateral glute isolation.

9. Dumbbell Frog Pump

Soles of feet together, knees out.

Dumbbell on hips.

Short-range glute pump, but very effective.

10. Dumbbell Lateral Step-Down

Stand on a step or bench.

Lower one foot to the side and push back up.

Hits glute medius for shaping and stability.

üí° Tips to Maximize Glute Activation

Use hip hinge movements for glute max.

Use long strides / forward lean for lunges and split squats.

At the top of hip thrusts, think ‚Äútuck your pelvis and squeeze.‚Äù

Control the negative (eccentric) for more tension.

If you want, I can make:
üî• A full dumbbell glute workout
üî• A glutes-only 20‚Äì30 min routine
üî• A weekly glute training plan

Just tell me!

